<a name="0.1_attraction"></a><h2>Attractions</h2>
All Souls' Church is conveniently located in downtown Stony Brook. It is next to <a href="http://www.stonybrookvillage.com/" target="_blank">Stony Brook Village Center</a> and is within few minutes' walking distance to <a href="http://www.avalonparkandpreserve.org/index.html" target="_blank">Avalon park and preserve</a>. It is very close to the <a href="http://www.stonybrook.edu/" target="_blank">Stony Brook University</a>, and <a href="http://stonybrookny.areaguides.net/attractions_results.html" target="_blank">a couple of museums</a>. Within short driving distance, I also like the west meadow beach which is next to the Old Field Club and the shops at the <a href="http://www.portjeff.com/aboutpj.html" target="_blank">Port Jefferson village</a>.
<ul>
<li>Stony Brook Univ. <a href="http://calendar.activedatax.com/stonybrook/EventList.aspx?fromdate=8%2f1%2f2007&amp;todate=8%2f31%2f2007&amp;display=Month&amp;view=DateTime" target="_blank">calendar and events</a> for October 2007
</li><li><a href="http://www.brookhaven.org/ThingsToDoInYourTown/ThingsToDoInYourTown/tabid/185/Default.aspx" target="_blank">Things to do</a> in Town of Brookhaven. Recommend the beaches and parks.
</li></ul>

